        <h4>Section 7 - Collection and Use of Other Data</h4>
        <p class="mb30">Our service providers and we may also collect and use the following types of data, referred to in this Policy as “Other Data”:<br>
          a)  Monitoring Data: This involves collecting and/or tracking other information such as demographic information, domain names, computer type, browser types, screen resolution, and other statistical data involving the use of this Site (“Monitoring Data”).  We use Monitoring Data to help us understand who uses this Site and to improve and market it, as well as our other websites and services.  Unless combined with Personal Data, Monitoring Data does not personally identify you or any other user, and we may use it for any purpose.<br>
          b)  Aggregated Data: This involves aggregating Personal Data in a manner such that the end-product does not personally identify you or any other user of this Site, for example, by using information to calculate the percentage of our users who have a particular telephone area code.  Such aggregate information may also be used for any purpose.<br>
          c)  HubSpot Analytics, Google Analytics:  We may use Google Analytics, HubSpot Analytics, Facebook and other similar programs which each use cookies and other similar technologies, to collect and analyse information about the use of this Site, other websites, apps and online resources and to report on activities and trends. <br>
          <br>
          You can read more about how these sites use your Personal Information here: <br>
          i)  https://www.google.com/intl/en/policies/privacy/. <br>
          ii) https://www.facebook.com/privacy/explanation. <br>
          <br>
          d)  Verification: We may use third-party services to verify that you are a human user.  Any information collected as part of such verification is subject to the privacy policy of the third-party service provider.<br>
          e)  IP Addresses: An Internet Protocol (IP) address is a number that is automatically assigned to the computer that you are using by your Internet Service Provider 
          (ISP).  This number is identified and logged automatically in our server log files whenever you visit this Site, along with the time(s) of your visit(s) and the page(s) that you visited.  We use IP addresses to understand how this Site is used by our users, to improve and administer this Site, to enhance user experience of this Site, to help diagnose problems with our server, and also to derive your approximate location from your IP address.<br>
        <h6>Cookies and Tools</h6>
        <p class="mb30">When you revisit this Site, we use cookies and Tools to understand how this Site is used and to customise and enhance the Internet experience of individual users.  For example, once you have completed the registration process, a cookie and/or Tool will be used to avoid having you register again. We believe cookies and Tools add value to the user experience. <br>
          f)  Cookies:  Cookies are data that a web server transfers to an individual’s computer for recordkeeping and other purposes.  We use cookies and other technologies to facilitate users’ internet experience, ongoing access to and use of our Site.  If you do not want information collected through the use of cookies, there is a simple procedure in most browsers that allows you to automatically decline cookies, or to be given the choice of declining or accepting the transfer of a particular cookie, or cookies from a particular website, to your computer.  If cookies are disabled, however, all features of this Site may not operate as intended. Information about disabling cookies can be found on your Internet browser provider’s web site.  This Site may have a Cookie Policy that applies to its use of cookies and other similar tracking technologies. If it does, then the Cookie Policy will apply in addition to this Policy. We may use the following types of cookies to improve how our Services function:<br>
          i)  Strictly Necessary: these cookies are essential to allow registered users to authenticate and perform account related functions, as well as to save the contents of virtual “carts” for e-commerce functionality.<br>
          ii) Analytics and Performance: Performance cookies collect information and understand on how users interact with our Services, including what pages are visited most, as well as other analytical data. <br>
          iii)  Functionality: These cookies are used to store preferences set by users, such as account name and language.<br>
          iv) Security: these cookies help identify and prevent potential security risks.<br>
          v)  Advertising: these cookies are used to display relevant advertising to users who use our Services, as well as to understand and report on the efficacy of adverts served on our Services. They track details such as the number of unique visitors, the number of times particular adverts have been displayed or clicked. They are also used to build user profiles, including showing you adverts based on products or Services you have viewed or acts you have taken. <br>
          vi) Third-Party / Embedded Content: Services hosted by us make use of different third-party applications and services to enhance the experience of our Services. As a result, cookies may be set by third parties, and used by them to track your online activity. We have no direct control over the information that is collected by these cookies.<br>
          g)  Tools:  Various common Internet tools such as ‘pixel tags,’ ‘action tags,’ ‘web beacons,’ ‘gif tags,’ ‘JavaScript’ or similar technologies (together, “Tools”) may be used in connection with Site pages and email messages in certain formats to, among other things, track the actions of Site users and email recipients, to determine the success of marketing campaigns and to compile statistics about Site usage and response rates.  Tools allow us to count users who have visited certain pages of this Site, to deliver Services, and to help determine the effectiveness of promotional or advertising campaigns.  When used in email messages in certain formats, Tools can tell the sender whether and when the email has been opened. </p>
        <h4>Section 8 - Behavioural Advertising</h4>
        <p class="mb30">As described above, TW Media may use third-party advertising companies and your Personal Information to provide you with targeted advertisements or marketing communications regarding products and Services we believe may be of interest to you based on information relating to your access to and use of this Site, our apps, other websites or online services on any of your devices. Third-party advertising companies may place or recognise a unique cookie on your browser (including through the use of pixel tags) and on other devices you use such as a mobile phone and a laptop. <br>
          <br>
